You are analyzing a fictional bank portal. 

The directory has a search feature to look up employees by name. However, due to insecure SQL query handling, the portal is vulnerable to Union-based SQL Injection.

Your task: exploit the vulnerability and retrieve the hidden flag stored in the backend database.

Category: SQL Injection - Union-based
Difficulty: Easy â€“ Medium

Subtle Hints for Players - 

The search form takes direct user input without sanitization.
Try to see how many columns the query is returning.
Once aligned, attempt to union your query with another table.
The flag is hidden inside the admin table.
